    "# DMAP — Decision-Making under Ambiguity and Poverty\n",
    "## Interactive Demo (Google Colab)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides a scaled-down, self-contained demo of the DMAP agent-based model.\n",
    "It runs entirely in Colab — no cluster required.\n",
    "\n",
    "**What the model does:**  \n",
    "Simulates agents on a grid who each decide whether to **follow rules** (safe, lower reward) or **break rules** (risky, higher reward) based on their wealth, their neighbors' wealth, and individual risk preferences drawn from Prospect Theory.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key mechanisms:**\n",
    "- Agents rank themselves relative to neighbors → the poorest become *desperate*\n",
    "- Desperate agents' utilities are amplified, making rule-breaking more attractive\n",
    "- Risk perception is heterogeneous: each agent draws individual `β` (uncertainty aversion) and `α` (probability sensitivity) from a t-distribution\n",
    "- Choices are probabilistic via a bounded-rational softmax rule\n",
    "\n",
    "**Full repo:** [github.com/blam3/ABM-poverty-uncertainty](https://github.com/blam3/ABM-poverty-uncertainty)"
   ],
   "id": "intro"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
